<h2>Solar Incentives in Pittsburgh</h2>

<p>Pittsburgh residents can take advantage of several solar incentives to reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, before stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Pennsylvania offers net metering through Duquesne Light, allowing customers to receive retail rate credits for excess electricity sent back to the grid. The state's Solar Renewable Energy Credit (SREC) program provides additional income, with SRECs typically trading between \$35-50 each, generating 4-6 credits annually for an average residential system. Property tax exemptions ensure that solar installations don't increase property tax assessments, while sales tax exemptions apply to solar equipment purchases. Some Pittsburgh neighborhoods may qualify for additional local incentives or group purchasing programs that can further reduce costs.</p>

<h2>Best Solar Companies in Pittsburgh</h2>

<p>When selecting a solar installer in Pittsburgh, prioritize companies with proper Pennsylvania contractor licensing, NABCEP-certified installers, and extensive local experience. Top-rated contractors should provide comprehensive warranties covering equipment (typically 20-25 years for panels, 10-12 years for inverters) and workmanship (minimum 10 years). Look for installers who are certified with major equipment manufacturers like Tesla, SunPower, or Enphase, as this ensures access to better warranties and technical support. Reputable companies will conduct thorough site assessments, provide detailed proposals with production estimates, handle all permitting and utility interconnection paperwork, and offer monitoring systems to track system performance. Check Better Business Bureau ratings, online reviews, and request references from recent customers. Avoid door-to-door sales tactics and always obtain multiple quotes from established local installers who understand Pittsburgh's specific climate challenges and building codes.</p>

